issue.title: Got an exception when trying to get contents

repository.name: jcabi-github
repository.description: Java Object-Oriented Wrapper of GitHub API, with a fake implementation of the entire GitHub API (for your tests)

issue.body:
Following `Contents.get()` method, we got an exception

``` java
final Repos repos = github().repos();
final Repo repo =  repos.get(new Coordinates.Simple("jcabi/jcabi-github"));
System.out.println(new Content.Smart(repo.contents().get("src/main/java/com/jcabi/github/Users.java")).url());
// #output https://api.github.com/repos/jcabi/jcabi-github/contents/src/main/java/com/jcabi/github/Users.java?ref=master
System.out.println(new Content.Smart(repo.contents().get("src/main/java/com/jcabi/github/mock")).url());
```

issue.title: what Contents#iterate() is doing?

repository.name: jcabi-github
repository.description: Java Object-Oriented Wrapper of GitHub API, with a fake implementation of the entire GitHub API (for your tests)

issue.body: I don't understand what `Contents#iterate()` is doing? This functionality is not provided by Github and we don't have an integration test for the method. I think it's obsolete and should be deleted.

body:
Well, I see the issue. The problem though is not a defect per se. If you ran the get, you are trying to access an object, simple content of an url, since you get a directory, you get a list of objects. So the correct approach would've been to call iterate instead, that is present in content and is intended to return an iterable collection of elements.
So, one possble solution is to create an exception that translates the JSonArray exception into an packege exception that will make it more user friendly, stating the preceding behavior.
Another solution, well, I'd love to know what you'd expect from that call.
Cheers
sorry about the delay in the response but I was unable to get to a pc for 4 days.
@aoxa Saying _Content doesn't support JsonArray reading_ I meant that it should read it (e.g. as a collection of `JsonObject`'s) without throwing any exception.
